WEBVTT

00:05.600 --> 00:09.300
[ Lorne ] Uh-huh.
Oh, I promise you. It'll be fabulous.

00:09.300 --> 00:11.500
Believe me,Jerry. Yes.

00:11.500 --> 00:14.500
It's <i>Grapes of Wrath</i>
in outer space. Uh-huh.

00:14.500 --> 00:17.500
Oh, it's got heart.
Yes, it's got laser battles.

00:17.500 --> 00:20.900
It's got a timely message
of interstellar poverty.

00:20.900 --> 00:24.800
Uh-huh. Listen, have your assistant
call my assistant.

00:24.800 --> 00:27.200
We'll set somethin' up.
Good enough.

00:27.200 --> 00:31.100
J.C., listen,
just got off the Nextel with Big B.

00:31.100 --> 00:34.100
Yeah, intrigued, but wants to know
who's playing Tom Joad. Uh-huh.

00:34.100 --> 00:37.400
Well, I'm pretty sure that
Henry Fonda's dead, sweetie.

00:37.400 --> 00:39.300
Yeah. ''Bring him back to life''?

00:39.300 --> 00:41.900
Let me talk to my science people.
Okay, no promises.

00:41.900 --> 00:44.600
- Directors. Harmonica!
- Lorney Tunes!

00:44.600 --> 00:47.500
Oh, the eyes, the hair, the dress.

00:47.500 --> 00:49.500
It's no wonder the fourth floor
has a crush on you.

00:49.500 --> 00:51.700
Hey, tell me, priceless.
Where do I find Angel?

00:51.700 --> 00:54.400
Just called. He's on his way back in
from a field mission.

00:54.400 --> 00:57.400
<i>Though I wouldn't, if I were you.</i>
<i>It sounds like he's in a mood.</i>

00:57.400 --> 01:00.600
Oh, don't worry, darlin'. I've pulled
the big boy out of many a broodfest.

01:00.600 --> 01:02.400
- It shouldn't be that--
<i>- [ Squishy Footsteps ]</i>

01:04.300 --> 01:06.300
Ew.

01:06.300 --> 01:08.800
Angel, how did the new
neural-intercept grenade work?

01:08.800 --> 01:11.500
It didn't.

01:11.500 --> 01:13.800
Right. I'll take it down to Fred,
have her look at it.

01:13.800 --> 01:15.700
Hey, Angelheart.
Wes, if you see Fred...

01:15.700 --> 01:17.600
can you have her
pencil me in for later?

01:17.600 --> 01:20.200
I've gotta talk to her about
Henry Fonda's big comeback.

01:20.200 --> 01:22.700
- [ Wesley ] All right.
- Angel, we gotta have a confab.

01:22.700 --> 01:25.600
<i>- Es muy importante.</i>
- Lorne--

01:25.600 --> 01:28.700
It's about the party. I've done
all I can do for the big to-do...

01:28.700 --> 01:31.800
but we've still got a few bugs
to comb out of the cootie garage.

01:31.800 --> 01:34.300
A bridge too far?
Let me try it again.

01:34.300 --> 01:37.000
Lorne, I've been out all night.
I'm beat up. I'm exhausted.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.900
I'm covered head to toe in Thraxis blood,
which actually kind of burns...

01:39.900 --> 01:42.100
so this is all gonna have to wait
until I take a shower.

01:42.100 --> 01:43.900
- You killed a Thraxis? But--
- Shower.

01:45.400 --> 01:49.100
Van, why don't we scratch the Thraxis
off of the invite list?

01:49.100 --> 01:51.600
And you got a copy of that print ad
we're gonna run this week?

01:51.600 --> 01:54.000
- Yeah. Right.
- What is this?

01:54.000 --> 01:56.400
''Wolfram and Hart
wants to be up your alley''?

01:56.400 --> 01:58.600
That's like a bus station
pickup line. Change it.

01:58.600 --> 02:00.800
On second thought, burn it.
Grab yourself a bagel or somethin' too.

02:00.800 --> 02:03.000
You look a little waxy.

02:04.100 --> 02:06.000
[ Sighs ]

02:09.600 --> 02:11.600
[ Sighs ]

02:13.000 --> 02:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:24.800 --> 02:27.200
Ooh, ouch.

02:27.200 --> 02:30.600
That's an adult-size bangaroo. Hello!

02:30.600 --> 02:33.800
- [ Groaning ]
<i>- Oh, Mr. Smiles?</i>

02:33.800 --> 02:36.100
Oh, come on.
You can't ignore me forever.

02:36.100 --> 02:38.800
- [ Sighs ]
- Well, fine.

02:38.800 --> 02:41.200
Looks like you're gonna have to
slap a Band Aid on that melon...

02:41.200 --> 02:44.600
<i>and draw a grin on that bewitching</i>
<i>green mug and go right back out there.</i>

02:44.600 --> 02:46.400
On the count of nine, sunshine.

02:46.400 --> 02:50.400
One, two, three--

02:50.600 --> 02:53.100
The show stops for no demon, Lorne.

02:53.100 --> 02:56.300
Four, five--
They're all waiting for you.

02:56.300 --> 02:58.000
<i>Six, seven--</i>

02:58.000 --> 03:00.600
They're counting on you.
Eight-- Comin' up on nine.

03:00.600 --> 03:04.400
<i>They're gonna eat you up</i>
<i>with a spoon because you're so...</i>

03:04.400 --> 03:06.600
<i>- scrumptious.!</i>
- Shut up!

03:16.300 --> 03:18.200
[ Sighs ]

04:32.600 --> 04:35.400
<i>[ Shower Running ]</i>

04:37.600 --> 04:39.600
<i>[ Shower Stops ]</i>

04:41.400 --> 04:43.300
<i>[ Eve ]</i>
<i>Hi.</i>

04:48.900 --> 04:52.100
The door was open.
Well, unlocked.

04:53.800 --> 04:56.000
Well, I had a key.

05:03.900 --> 05:06.800
<i>- [ Key Clatters ]</i>
<i>- So, uh, wow.</i>

05:06.800 --> 05:09.900
You take a long shower for a guy.

05:09.900 --> 05:11.800
Were we having some
gentleman's time?

05:11.800 --> 05:14.100
- ''Gentleman's''?
<i>- I mean, I understand.</i>

05:14.100 --> 05:16.400
You're running the whole circus now,
a lot of pressure.

05:16.400 --> 05:19.900
Especially with your hands-on policy.
No pun intended.

05:21.100 --> 05:23.600
I'm sure you could use a release.

05:23.600 --> 05:26.300
No releasing,just bathing.
That's what one does...

05:26.300 --> 05:30.700
<i>after bashing open a demonic pinata</i>
<i>full of rancid Tabasco.</i>

05:30.700 --> 05:33.600
- What do you want, Eve?
- You stood me up.

05:33.600 --> 05:37.000
<i>We had a 7:30, Angel.</i>
<i>A meeting.</i>

05:37.000 --> 05:41.000
- Oh, right. Uh, I'll get my pants.
<i>- [ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

05:42.700 --> 05:45.800
- So how's it going, Angel?
- [ Sighs ]

05:45.800 --> 05:48.400
I don't know how
to answer that question.

05:49.600 --> 05:53.000
I don't know. Good. Bad.

05:53.000 --> 05:56.000
I spent years doing everything
I could to bring this company down.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.600
Now I'm the C.E.O., and I have to
question every move I make...

05:58.600 --> 06:01.600
because any one of them could be
exactly what the senior partners want.

06:01.600 --> 06:03.800
So, no, I have no idea how it's goin'.

06:03.800 --> 06:07.000
Hey, at least you can still get
your nocturnal jollies...

06:07.000 --> 06:09.600
saving the downtrodden
from things that go bump in the night.

06:09.600 --> 06:11.900
You said it yourself--
''Everyone needs a release.''

06:11.900 --> 06:14.200
No, I said you need a release.

06:14.200 --> 06:16.100
Not everyone bottles
all this stuff up like you.

06:16.100 --> 06:18.300
- I don't bottle.
- You bottle.

06:18.300 --> 06:19.900
- I don't bottle.
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]</i>

06:21.000 --> 06:23.100
[ Groaning ]

06:26.600 --> 06:28.600
Why does it look like
we're havin' a party in here?

06:28.600 --> 06:30.600
Maybe 'cause we're
havin' a party in here.

06:30.600 --> 06:32.700
The Wolfram and Hart Halloween bash?

06:32.700 --> 06:35.300
<i>Ring a bell? Biggest event</i>
<i>on the company calendar?</i>

06:35.300 --> 06:37.700
I sent you a small
forest's worth of memos on it.

06:37.700 --> 06:40.700
- We're havin' it here?
- You see what I'm up against?

06:40.700 --> 06:43.400
That's what our 7:30 was about, Angel--
your party.

06:43.400 --> 06:47.200
- My party?
- Yeah, listen, here's the snafu in a nutshell, top cat.

06:47.200 --> 06:49.300
Uh, nobody's comin'.

06:50.800 --> 06:54.100
Well, some people are comin',
but the right people--

06:54.100 --> 06:56.500
the A-list people--
they seem to be giving it a miss.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.000
- And if they don't show up,
this shindig is gonna be a bust.
- Good.

06:59.000 --> 07:01.500
- Good?
- Yeah, I wasn't too crazy
about this thing to begin with.

07:01.500 --> 07:03.700
I mean, we are talking about
our clients, right?

07:03.700 --> 07:06.400
Our evil clients. Not the sort of folks
I'd really like to show a good time.

07:06.400 --> 07:09.800
I'd be a lot happier if the whole thing
just kind of fell through.

07:09.800 --> 07:12.400
- Then we can get back to--
- [ Laughs ] Okay! Okay, you're killin' me!

07:12.400 --> 07:15.000
Can't you just feel up
the big picture, Mr. Magoo?

07:15.000 --> 07:17.300
It's not about good and evil.
It's about party.

07:17.300 --> 07:20.200
Party! Capital P,
rhymes with me.

07:20.200 --> 07:22.600
I'm about to have a stroke here,
'cause you're killin' me!

07:24.700 --> 07:29.500
Listen, I can see that
you're in a state...

07:29.500 --> 07:33.400
a mood, a snit, even.

07:33.400 --> 07:37.700
So what say we talk about this once
you've calmed down a bit?

07:41.800 --> 07:43.700
Yeah, sure. That's fine with--

07:43.700 --> 07:46.200
Great. Your office, 25 minutes.

07:50.900 --> 07:53.300
- Was Angel mad?
- Shouldn't he be?

07:53.300 --> 07:55.400
We sent him out there with
a defective piece of weaponry.

07:55.400 --> 07:57.900
Which ''we'' are we talking about?

07:57.900 --> 08:01.700
Fred, these techno-mystical hybrids
are a complicated affair.

08:02.000 --> 08:04.600
I don't know.
They seem kind of simple to me.

08:04.600 --> 08:08.300
<i>It's just a little handheld,</i>
<i>spell-casting robot, right?</i>

08:08.300 --> 08:11.800
So it's either the robot or the spell
that we have a problem with.

08:11.800 --> 08:14.700
Well, the grenade's core
enchantment looks operational...

08:14.700 --> 08:17.300
so I think we're talking about
a faulty trigger mechanism.

08:17.300 --> 08:19.700
No. Wait a minute.
I designed that mechanism myself.

08:19.700 --> 08:22.000
<i>Yeah, that's right, and I machined it.</i>

08:22.000 --> 08:25.700
It was beautiful work
on both counts, if I may say.

08:25.700 --> 08:28.500
- You may.
- [ Chuckles ]

08:28.500 --> 08:30.700
I agree, as a sculptural piece.

08:30.700 --> 08:32.900
But the device's trigger
may not have been refined enough...

08:32.900 --> 08:34.799
to actually trigger the effect.

08:34.799 --> 08:36.700
Happy Halloween, kids.

08:36.700 --> 08:39.400
<i>How do you know your spell-casters</i>
<i>didn't screw up the payload?</i>

08:39.400 --> 08:43.100
Because I went over the work,
and I got that knowing feeling
you get when you know something.

08:43.100 --> 08:46.200
- Trick or treat?
- Hi, Lorne.
- Hi.

08:46.200 --> 08:48.800
What do you say we put away your
little sci-fi toys for a little bit, huh?

08:48.800 --> 08:51.400
Maybe we could talk about
something a little more important...

08:51.400 --> 08:53.900
like my monster mash.

08:53.900 --> 08:56.100
Oh, yeah, your party.

08:56.100 --> 08:59.100
<i>Our</i> party, Tweety Bird, which,
by the way, is dying on the vine.

08:59.100 --> 09:02.600
I could really, really, really use
some help from you guys. Some backup.

09:02.600 --> 09:05.600
I wasn't really planning on going.

09:07.400 --> 09:10.200
Wes, do you hear this crazy talk?

09:10.200 --> 09:13.800
Uh, well, I really hadn't given
much thought to going myself.

09:15.100 --> 09:17.000
<i>Et tu,</i> Brutuses?

09:17.000 --> 09:20.300
Why is it so hard to get anyone
to have any fun around here?

09:20.300 --> 09:22.400
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>You should go.</i>

09:22.400 --> 09:25.500
It's the Halloween blowout
to end all blowouts.

09:25.500 --> 09:27.500
Last year, uh,
[ Chuckling ]

09:27.500 --> 09:30.100
<i>they took a bunch of cows...</i>

09:30.100 --> 09:32.800
and put them in this
giant wicker effigy of Krishna...

09:32.800 --> 09:34.700
doused it with Sambuca and--

09:37.300 --> 09:41.600
Uh, well, anyway,
it's a hell of a good time.

09:43.500 --> 09:46.500
I really wanna get this operational
before Angel goes out again.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.900
- Yes, I'll stay too.
- Wha--

09:48.900 --> 09:51.900
- I'm sure we can work it out together.
- No.

09:51.900 --> 09:56.600
No, no, no, no, no, no, no! Wes, Fred,
you're coming. Look at yourselves.

09:56.600 --> 09:59.000
You're wound tighter
than Martha Stewart's watch.

09:59.000 --> 10:03.700
Isn't there anyone else who could fix
the little boo-boos on this thing?

10:04.900 --> 10:06.800
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>I can do that.</i>

10:06.800 --> 10:10.000
It's probably the trigger
mechanism anyway.

10:10.000 --> 10:13.000
Great. Problem solved.

10:13.000 --> 10:16.100
I'll see you two in Angel's office,
1 5 minutes.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.600
<i>[ Knocking On Door ]</i>

10:20.700 --> 10:22.500
- Hey, Lorne.
- Hey, hey.

10:22.500 --> 10:26.000
Uh, sorry to interrupt.
Not to be a pest...

10:26.000 --> 10:28.400
but I just wanted to go over
a little stratego, amigo.

10:28.400 --> 10:31.300
- Sorry?
- Um, you're my big gun, Gunn.

10:31.300 --> 10:33.200
<i>Ace in hole.</i>
<i>Ball in pocket.</i>

10:33.200 --> 10:35.200
You're the key on my kite string.

10:35.200 --> 10:36.900
Okay.

10:36.900 --> 10:39.900
We gotta turn Angel around
on this whole party idea.

10:39.900 --> 10:42.700
- We do?
- I know he's the boss and everything...

10:42.700 --> 10:46.000
<i>but you're up and coming here, and it's time</i>
<i>for you to spread your wings, legal eagle.</i>

10:46.000 --> 10:48.800
From now on, I want you
to stake out your territory...

10:48.800 --> 10:50.600
and I want you to keep it staked.

10:50.600 --> 10:53.000
Stake. Territory. Sure.

10:53.000 --> 10:56.500
Lorne, I'm a little busy right now.
I have a deposition to get ready for.

10:56.500 --> 10:58.900
- But I will definitely get to that.
- Great.

10:58.900 --> 11:02.900
Just what I wanted to hear.
Angel's office, 1 0 minutes.

11:02.900 --> 11:05.200
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

11:12.100 --> 11:14.700
In my day, no self-respecting
creature of the night...

11:14.700 --> 11:17.200
went out on All Hallow's Eve.

11:17.200 --> 11:21.000
<i>We left that to the poseurs-- the blighters</i>
<i>who had to dress up and try to be scary.</i>

11:23.800 --> 11:27.200
Magic windows.
Will the perks never end?

11:27.200 --> 11:29.000
[ Italian ]

11:31.000 --> 11:33.000
Ciao.

11:33.000 --> 11:35.200
- What'd I miss?
- Us waiting.

11:35.200 --> 11:38.000
Oh, right. Sorry.

11:38.000 --> 11:40.700
So, uh, Angel, we just wanted
to take a moment...

11:40.700 --> 11:44.700
and emphasize how important
this party really is to us.

11:44.700 --> 11:46.300
I gotta say Lorne is right.

11:46.300 --> 11:49.000
We gotta show all the big-bads
that the new regime is here to stay...

11:49.000 --> 11:51.600
<i>which, for the most part,</i>
<i>boils down to image.</i>

11:51.600 --> 11:53.800
And image-wise, if this party
doesn't kick ass, we lose face.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.800
And believe me, Milk Dud,
speaking as the head...

11:55.800 --> 11:58.400
of your P.R. department,
we need all the face we can get.

11:58.400 --> 12:00.800
- ''Milk Dud''?
- Said with affection.

12:00.800 --> 12:03.600
Okay, listen, I understand the whole
keeping-up-appearances concept...

12:03.600 --> 12:06.900
but everyone comin' to this thing
is unrepentant, dyed-in-the-wool evil.

12:06.900 --> 12:09.400
Angel, a good host just doesn't
make these sort of judgments.

12:09.400 --> 12:12.800
We don't know how many of them are holdin'
grudges against us or against each other.

12:12.800 --> 12:15.700
<i>It's a perfect recipe for</i>
<i>an out-of-control bloodbath.</i>

12:15.700 --> 12:18.300
That's describing every good party
I've ever been to. [ Laughs ]

12:20.400 --> 12:23.900
Listen, Angel, don't worry about a thing.
This is my forte.

12:23.900 --> 12:27.000
<i>I ran Caritas for years--</i>
<i>a nightclub with an open-door policy.</i>

12:27.000 --> 12:28.900
The good, the bad,
the hideously ugly--

12:28.900 --> 12:30.900
They all bellied up to my demon bar...

12:30.900 --> 12:33.800
but they all played nicely
together while they were there.

12:33.800 --> 12:36.600
This is exactly the kind of ethical
tightrope you've got to walk now.

12:36.600 --> 12:39.400
<i>Which brings up another point--</i>
<i>your employees.</i>

12:39.400 --> 12:43.400
- Also evil.
- Here's your blood, bossy.

12:43.400 --> 12:45.200
[ Clears Throat ]
Boss.

12:45.200 --> 12:49.800
<i>Some of them,yes. But all of them</i>
<i>work hard for this firm.</i>

12:49.800 --> 12:53.800
And Halloween--
Well, around here it's like Christmas.

12:54.000 --> 12:56.600
Simply put, this is a morale thing.

12:56.600 --> 12:59.800
[ Scoffs ] Good luck.
Morale around here stinks.

12:59.800 --> 13:03.500
- What?
- Uh-huh. Everybody thinks you suck.

13:03.500 --> 13:07.800
<i>Well, come on, boss. They're all out there</i>
<i>sweating through their Matsudas...</i>

13:07.800 --> 13:11.800
worried if you're gonna ax them or,
you know, ax them.

13:11.800 --> 13:13.900
Okay, look.
Hey, I haven't--

13:15.200 --> 13:18.500
Okay, look, I may have killed
a couple of them--

13:18.500 --> 13:20.600
And several clients.

13:20.600 --> 13:22.900
And maybe some potential clients.

13:22.900 --> 13:26.500
Why do you think my R.S.V.P. list is only
a fifth of the size of last year's?

13:26.500 --> 13:28.600
- It's you, babe.
- What do they think--

13:28.600 --> 13:30.900
I'm throwin' this thing
so I can slaughter them?

13:35.100 --> 13:37.900
Fine. I surrender.
Go ahead, Lorne.

13:37.900 --> 13:40.600
Put on your best dog and pony.
I won't get in the way.

13:40.600 --> 13:43.300
I don't want you to sit back
and just let it happen, Angel.

13:43.300 --> 13:47.000
<i>- I need you to get out there and make it happen.</i>
- What does that mean?

13:47.000 --> 13:49.500
<i>[ Lorne ]</i>
<i>Archduke Sebassis...</i>

13:49.500 --> 13:52.900
bona fide nobility
for the fiery down under...

13:52.900 --> 13:54.800
commands over 40 legions.

13:54.800 --> 13:58.200
He's the living end of a pure bloodline
of demonic royalty.

13:58.200 --> 14:01.200
- Great.Just great.
<i>- Yeah, well, also the very peak...</i>

14:01.200 --> 14:03.100
of the A-list mountain.

14:03.100 --> 14:05.400
He's the crown jewel
of the underworld jet set.

14:05.400 --> 14:07.800
If we convince him to come,
[ Chuckles ]

14:07.800 --> 14:10.700
all the other glitterati
will just domino in right behind him...

14:10.700 --> 14:13.500
and then--
then we'll be in business.

14:15.600 --> 14:17.700
This really matters to you,
doesn't it?

14:17.700 --> 14:19.900
Of course. The new Wolfram and Hart.
I mean, we have to--

14:19.900 --> 14:25.100
No. I mean, this really matters
to you... personally.

14:28.700 --> 14:31.500
Yeah. You know, Angel, I--

14:31.500 --> 14:34.000
I don't have superhuman strength...

14:34.000 --> 14:36.200
and I'm not a fighter...

14:36.200 --> 14:38.200
<i>and quantum physics</i>
<i>makes me nauseous.</i>

14:38.200 --> 14:40.500
<i>I barely made a passing grade</i>
<i>in mystical studies.</i>

14:41.600 --> 14:43.500
But I'm on your team.

14:44.900 --> 14:47.000
<i>This is something I can do.</i>

14:47.000 --> 14:52.400
I believe it has a purpose that can
help you, even if you don't.

14:53.800 --> 14:56.600
I'm here, aren't I?
I agreed to this.

14:56.600 --> 14:58.500
No, you did. You did.

14:58.500 --> 15:00.400
And I promise you won't regret it.

15:00.400 --> 15:04.200
<i>But, hey, let's say that you let me</i>
<i>do most of the talking, huh?</i>

15:04.200 --> 15:08.200
<i>You just kind of smile and try not</i>
<i>to rip anybody apart, okay?</i>

15:09.600 --> 15:13.500
So, this is the mighty Angel.

15:14.600 --> 15:17.000
I've been told
many things about you.

15:17.000 --> 15:19.200
A bit of a restless frog, hmm?

15:19.200 --> 15:23.000
<i>Making lots of waves</i>
<i>in your little swamp.</i>

15:23.000 --> 15:26.400
Yeah. Well, I'm just trying
to keep the fly population down.

15:26.400 --> 15:30.100
